pullRequest.body:
Add LaTeX descriptions for all `Icc`/`Ico`/`Ioc`/`Ioo`/`Iio`/`Ioi`/`Iic`/`Ici` intervals. Following [this zulip thread](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/notation.20for.20intervals).

---

bors merge

Pull request successfully merged into master.

Build succeeded:
  * [Lint style](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/11237158967/job/31238936397)
  * [Build](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/11237158967/job/31238937705)

> You're missing a space after each last dollar sign. 

Thanks, fixed.

> Could you do the finset ones as well? 

Done!

```suggestion
/-- Left-infinite right-closed interval $(-\infty, b]$ -/
```
to match the argument name

Maybe
```suggestion
/-- `Icc a b` is the left-open right-open interval $(a, b)$ -/
```
since otherwise you don't actually see what `a` and `b` refer to. Feel free to wait for other reviewer votes before changing it.
You have a typo in your suggestion: should be `Ioo`, not `Icc`.
I fixed it while accepting the suggestion (that I otherwise found correct).
Arguably we should rename `a` to `b` here to match  `Iic`.

One more option:
```suggestion
/-- `Ioo a b` is $(a, b)$, the left-open right-open interval. -/
```
which puts the "punchline" as early in the docstring as possible.
(whether you prefer this or the original, please add the trailing `.`s)
I honestly prefer the first, but will add all trailing `.`s

```suggestion
/-- `Iio b` is the left-infinite right-open interval $(-∞, b)$ -/
```
I am happy to do so, but why? I mean, isn't LaTeX well rendered?
LaTeX isn't rendered in VSCode.
Can you do `Finset.Iio` +3 as well?
OMG, I forgot. Done (and fixed some error in the doc, in passing). What about `uIcc`? I am not adding any doc there, since it uses `Icc` and I have added it for this, but you tell me.
I think you can punt `uIcc` etc to a later PR, since I think the appropriate notation is less clear there.

pullRequest.title: [Merged by Bors] - docs: add latex doc for `Set` and `Finset` intervals
